race.comment: HEADSTOCK (6) ran below expectations last time after being in the firing line on the turn at Kyneton, finishing sixth and beaten 6 lengths starting at $6.50. This doesn't look as hard so he is set to turn things around. PARCH (5) is back at the races for the first time since February 14. Worth noting he filled a minor placing when returning from a spell last time in work over 1118m at Geelong. Looks a winning chance, especially with the blinkers going on. ZEMGRINDA (9) finished second last time over 1000m at Echuca when resuming from a spell, beaten 0.8 lengths. Placed to advantage so expect a big run. INFINITE MATRIX (8) wasn't beaten far at this track two starts ago and will put itself on-speed and give itself every chance.
